Reasoning: The paper deals with the computation of stopping sets and stopping distance in Tanner graphs, which are commonly used in coding theory and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves computational complexity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the problem of finding stopping sets and stopping distance can be viewed as a graph problem, which could place the paper in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
